The three Watatsumis are speculated to correspodn to three historical fishing practices Uwatsu Watatsumi no Kami (sea surface god), Nakatsu Watatsumi no Kami (middle depth god) and Sokotsu Watatsumi no Kami (depths god).<ref name=":023">{{Cite book |last=Rambelli |first=F |title=The Sea and The Sacred in Japan |publisher=Bloomsbury Academic Publishing |year=2018 |isbn=978-1350062870 |location=Camden |pages=}}</ref>{{rp|xxviii}}

